The paper discusses a novel approach to rank vertices in a heterogeneous graph of papers and authors, specifically in the context of evaluating research activities. This falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) as it involves ranking and analyzing information. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of DBLP and CiteseerX datasets, which are commonly used in the fields of Digital Libraries (cs.DL) and Information Science (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the analysis of social networks (cs.SOC) and the use of algorithms for ranking (cs.DB).
